WEBVTT

00:05.880 --> 00:09.008
(circular saw grinding)

00:12.470 --> 00:15.640
(grinding pauses, restarts)

00:17.600 --> 00:20.729
(grinding continues)

00:21.354 --> 00:23.565
Hey! Hey!

00:23.648 --> 00:26.526
-(grinding stops)
-It's a little bit early
to be doing that, isn't it?

00:26.609 --> 00:29.654
Sorry! Sorry. Almost done.

00:29.738 --> 00:31.072
It's, uh...

00:31.156 --> 00:32.782
it's 12:30.

00:33.783 --> 00:34.743
Fuck, really?

00:36.411 --> 00:37.912
Yeah.

00:40.248 --> 00:41.791
Nice underpants.

00:44.669 --> 00:46.588
Oh. Um...

00:47.547 --> 00:49.257
-They're my mom's.
-Oh.

00:49.340 --> 00:51.342
Vintage.

00:51.426 --> 00:54.095
She has great taste.

00:54.179 --> 00:56.306
She's a shopper. (laughs)

00:56.389 --> 00:58.558
(door opens, shuts)

00:58.641 --> 01:01.770
(light theme playing)

01:07.442 --> 01:10.153
Sammy! Over here!

01:10.236 --> 01:11.780
-Have a seat.
-Michael: Hey.

01:11.863 --> 01:14.282
-Hi. Sorry I'm late.
-Joel: It's okay.

01:14.365 --> 01:16.284
-Fred: Join us.
-(cafe chatter)

01:16.367 --> 01:18.995
Okay. What's everybody gettin'?

01:19.078 --> 01:21.164
I'm gonna order the eggs,
but I'm warning you,

01:21.247 --> 01:23.583
-I'm gonna have burger envy.
-Michael: Yeah?

01:23.666 --> 01:25.502
Joel:
You know, you can get
this without cheese.

01:25.585 --> 01:27.504
-Okay.
-'Cause of your tummy.

01:27.587 --> 01:29.923
You really
say "tummy"?

01:30.006 --> 01:33.134
-What do you call it?
-Stomach!

01:33.218 --> 01:35.428
No, but I-I love you kids.
What are you gonna eat, Sammy?

01:35.512 --> 01:37.138
Okay. Well, maybe I'll
start with some coffee.

01:37.222 --> 01:38.681
Michael:
So that means
Bloody Marys then?

01:38.765 --> 01:41.184
You can get Bloody Marys.
We're all together.
This is a big one.

01:41.267 --> 01:44.687
(laughter)

01:44.771 --> 01:47.649
So, what are you going to
sing next choir practice?

01:47.732 --> 01:50.276
You know, I don't know.
He-he tricked me
into it last time,

01:50.360 --> 01:52.904
so I... I don't know.
I gotta think about it.

01:52.987 --> 01:56.115
-How is everything?
-So good.

01:56.199 --> 01:57.992
Thank you, sir. Ma'am.

01:58.076 --> 02:00.787
Hey, you got it right
the first time.
Alright, beat it.

02:00.870 --> 02:02.121
(laughs)

02:02.205 --> 02:04.332
-Ai-yi-yi. Alright.
-(phone buzzing)

02:04.415 --> 02:07.293
I said it was on me,
and you're cleaning me out.

02:07.377 --> 02:09.504
-But it has been
my absolute pleasure.
-(Michael laughing)

02:09.587 --> 02:10.839
Anyone else leaving?

02:10.922 --> 02:11.881
Yeah.

02:11.965 --> 02:14.551
I am gonna stay
and finish my coffee.

02:14.634 --> 02:16.719
-Me, too.
-Michael: Oh.

02:19.013 --> 02:21.432
-Good to see you, Sam.
-Yeah, good to see you, Mike.

02:23.518 --> 02:27.981
You know, I didn't know this was
gonna be, like, a whole thing.

02:28.064 --> 02:30.108
-What, brunch?
-Yeah, it's kinda like

02:30.191 --> 02:31.776
a non-sanctioned group activity.

02:31.860 --> 02:33.695
There's only four of us.

02:33.778 --> 02:35.864
I... How'd I do?

02:35.947 --> 02:38.491
-I think you did well.
-(phone vibrating)

02:38.575 --> 02:41.244
Oh, my fucking sister.

02:41.327 --> 02:43.037
Hi.

02:43.121 --> 02:45.039
When I get there.

02:45.123 --> 02:46.374
Alright.

02:46.457 --> 02:50.086
You know what?
I, uh, I have to go by
my sister's store.

02:50.169 --> 02:52.839
-Oh, do you wanna
walk with me?
-Sure.

02:52.922 --> 02:55.216
Okay. Oh, Fred left
a lot of money.

02:55.300 --> 02:56.968
He's like a big tipper, huh?

02:57.051 --> 02:59.262
Yeah, especially for waiters
who feel uncomfortable.

02:59.345 --> 03:01.764
What does he teach, anyway?

03:01.848 --> 03:03.558
He's really big
into farmy stuff.

03:03.641 --> 03:06.144
He's the head
of the entire...

03:06.227 --> 03:08.521
I wanna say
Dirt Department?

03:08.605 --> 03:10.148
-(laughs)
-Huh.

03:10.857 --> 03:12.692
Well, this is me.

03:15.111 --> 03:18.156
-Oh. Are you coming in?
-Sure!

03:18.239 --> 03:20.408
Okay, well, if you like
knickknacks and doodads,

03:20.491 --> 03:22.160
you're gonna love this place.

03:22.243 --> 03:23.369
(door bell ringing)

03:26.915 --> 03:29.500
-(plastic crinkling)
-I've never figured out
who buys this shit.

03:29.584 --> 03:31.294
Oh, totally.

03:31.377 --> 03:33.463
-Joel! Hi!
-(Joel laughs)

03:33.546 --> 03:36.382
-Joel: Hey, Tricia.
-I didn't know you
two were friends.

03:36.466 --> 03:39.677
Cute.
Oh, cardamom.

03:39.761 --> 03:41.304
-We both said that you
would love that one.
-Yep.

03:41.387 --> 03:44.349
Oh. Thank you, Charity.
You know me well. (laughs)

03:44.432 --> 03:46.434
-(whispers): Do you have
a house account here?
-No...

03:46.517 --> 03:47.602
Good.

03:47.685 --> 03:49.103
I need you Monday night.

03:49.187 --> 03:50.813
I need your handwriting.

03:50.897 --> 03:52.190
We have our event
coming up for Crazy Dayz.

03:52.273 --> 03:54.067
It's really important,
and I really need you

03:54.150 --> 03:55.276
for the invitations.

03:55.360 --> 03:57.362
By the way,
who would've thought this one

03:57.445 --> 03:59.280
would have such
beautiful handwriting?

03:59.364 --> 04:00.949
-Joel: I would.
-Tricia: Yeah?

04:01.032 --> 04:03.743
-Can you?
-Sure.

04:03.826 --> 04:06.829
Great. Please bring
exactly that spirit.

04:08.206 --> 04:10.792
-And thank you!
-Sam: Yep.

04:10.875 --> 04:12.877
Okay, you ready?

04:12.961 --> 04:15.380
I-I don't need this.

04:15.463 --> 04:18.841
-(door bell ringing)
-I always do that.
I always roll over for her.

04:18.925 --> 04:20.218
Oh, hey, Rick.

04:20.301 --> 04:22.095
-Hey, Sam.
-How you doing?

04:23.846 --> 04:27.517
(whispers):
Oh my god. I almost forgot that
I saw him at choir practice!

04:27.600 --> 04:29.519
Oh yeah. I've seen
him there before.

04:29.602 --> 04:31.479
Wait, what?

04:31.562 --> 04:33.064
What?

04:33.147 --> 04:35.566
Oh my god! Is Rick gay?

04:35.650 --> 04:38.987
-No, you don't have
to be gay to go.
-I know, but...

04:39.070 --> 04:41.239
Something's going on.

04:41.322 --> 04:44.158
(truck brakes squeak,
engine cuts)

04:50.206 --> 04:53.543
Hey! You found
your pants.

04:53.626 --> 04:55.420
Sam:
Oh. (laughs)

04:55.503 --> 04:57.714
Yeah, I'm, um, mixin' it up.

04:57.797 --> 04:59.132
(car door shuts)

05:03.803 --> 05:05.388
How's it going?

05:08.808 --> 05:10.351
I've seen you come
and go for a year,

05:10.435 --> 05:12.353
and you never said
"hi" till this morning.

05:13.104 --> 05:14.647
Yeah, um...

05:15.440 --> 05:16.816
Well,

05:16.899 --> 05:19.068
I guess I'm trying out
being a people-person.

05:19.152 --> 05:22.030
-How's that working for you?
-(scoffs) I'm not sure.

05:22.113 --> 05:24.323
(both laugh)

05:26.159 --> 05:27.452
I like your trellis.

05:27.535 --> 05:29.787
Oh. (scoffs) Thanks.

05:29.871 --> 05:32.707
I was gonna espalier
a Bougainvillea,

05:32.790 --> 05:35.001
-but they go to
shit in the cold.
-Um,

05:35.084 --> 05:38.337
well, I have,
if you're interested,

05:38.421 --> 05:40.089
a pile of dirt and sticks.

05:40.173 --> 05:42.091
I'm kinda in
the planning stages.

05:42.175 --> 05:43.551
-Oh, cool.
-(laughs)

05:43.634 --> 05:45.762
I'm just kidding.
I can't keep anything
alive over here.

05:45.845 --> 05:47.513
-(laughs)
-Like Holly.

05:47.597 --> 05:51.059
-(gasps) Oh my god!
-Shit. Uh, too far.

05:51.142 --> 05:52.351
She had a dark sense of humor,
so I thought--

05:52.435 --> 05:53.811
No, she did. No, it's fine.

05:53.895 --> 05:56.105
-It's okay, I just did
not see that coming.
-Are you sure?

05:56.189 --> 05:58.066
-(sighs)
-Yeah. (laughs)

05:58.149 --> 06:00.151
I really-- I really liked her.

06:00.234 --> 06:02.612
-Yeah. She's pretty great.
-Yeah.

06:03.988 --> 06:06.199
Um, well...

06:07.241 --> 06:10.495
My name is Sam.

06:11.329 --> 06:14.082
My name is Drew.

06:14.165 --> 06:15.541
D-R-E-W Drew?

06:15.625 --> 06:17.251
That's all four letters.

06:17.335 --> 06:19.962
-All four. Like "fuck."
-Yeah. (laughs)

06:20.046 --> 06:22.799
Oh my god. You know, this has
really been nice talking to you.

06:22.882 --> 06:25.301
-Nice talking to you.
-Probably won't
happen again, but...

06:25.384 --> 06:27.595
-Alright, have a good life.
-Yeah. (laughs)

06:28.221 --> 06:29.764
You, too.

06:29.847 --> 06:33.434
-I'm gonna go make
myself a sandwich.
-Enjoy that.

06:33.518 --> 06:35.686
(mouthing)

